title: Welcome To My Blog
text:
Welcome to my blog entitled, “INSERT TITLE HERE”. This is my first blog post.

1 Instructions
In this assignment, you will be creating your “Welcome to my Blog” post by editing the contents of this document. Please follow the instructions below:

In the header (above), change the author name to your full name and change the date.
Feel free to change the post image if you’d like (you’ll need to add the image to the folder and update the file name above).
Insert a blog title.
Introduce yourself and tell the readers about yourself (nothing you don’t feel comfortable sharing).
Say what your blog articles will be about (generally) and why you are excited to write about that.
Say something about the unique perspective you will bring to writing about that topic.
Remove the “Instructions” section when you post your article.

Notes:

This is a public blog. The whole world can see it. This can increase the visibility of your work and profile. You can expect that anything you write online is permanent. My strong suggestion is: Don’t write anything that you wouldn’t feel comfortable with your parents or (current or) future employer seeing.
The writing should be your own!
For all graphics, you should either a) create them yourself or b) use only those graphics that you have the license to use. You can use graphics with a Creative Commons license as long as you follow the terms of the license (e.g., cite the original, indicate if you make any changes, etc). To find graphics that have a Creative Commons license, when using Google Image Search, select: “Tools” > “Usage Rights” > “Creative Commons Licenses”.
